[1] Case updates
- Sun 10 Feb 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=8de649dc78

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 9 Feb 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 811, of which 750 are confirmed and 61 are probable.
In total, there were 510 deaths (449 confirmed and 61 probable) and 276 people cured.
- 148 suspected cases under investigation.
- 5 new confirmed cases, 2 in Katwa, 2 in Butembo and 1 Vuhovi.
- 5 new deaths of confirmed cases: 3 community deaths, 2 in Katwa and 1 in Vuhovi, 2 deaths in ETCs, including 1 at the Butembo ETC and 1 at the Katwa ETC.
- 3 new recoveries, including 2 exits from the Butembo ETC and 1 from the Katwa ETC.

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 77 188 people have been vaccinated, including 20 512 in Beni [North Kivu], 19 391 in Katwa [North Kivu], 8601 in Butembo [North Kivu], 6076 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 2746 in Kalunguta [North Kivu], 2321 in Goma [North Kivu], 2200 in Komanda [Ituri], 1844 in Oicha [North Kivu], 663 in Mandima [Ituri], 1283 in Kayina [North Kivu], 1272 in Kyondo [North Kivu], 1157 in Karisimbi [North Kivu], 1054 in Bunia [Ituri], 973 in Vuhovi [North Kivu], 920 in Masereka [North Kivu], 744 in Mutwanga [North Kivu], 700 in Lubero [North Kivu], 590 in Rutshuru [North Kivu], 567 in Biena [North Kivu], 527 in Nyankunde [Ituri], 510 at Musienene [North Kivu], 355 at Tchomia [Ituri], 306 at Mangurujipa [North Kivu], 254 at Alimbongo [North Kivu], 207 at Kirotshe [North Kivu], 180 at Rwampara [Ituri], 125 at Nyiragongo [North Kivu], 97 at Watsa [Haut-Uele], and 13 at Kisangani [Tshopo].
- The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 19 May 2018.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteurs Mary Marshall and Kunihiko Iizuka

- Sat 9 Feb 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=ec1fc46f2b

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 8 Feb 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 806, of which 745 are confirmed and 61 are probable.
In total, there were 505 deaths (444 confirmed and 61 probable) and 273 people cured.
- 190 suspected cases under investigation.
- 6 new confirmed cases in Katwa.
- 3 new deaths of confirmed cases: 1 community death in Katwa, 2 deaths at the Butembo ETC
- 2 new recoveries released from Butembo ETC.

News of the response
New probable cases in Katwa [North Kivu]
----------------------------------------
- 7 new probable cases (historical deaths) have been validated retrospectively in the health zone of Katwa. These are people who became ill between November and December 2018 and who died between November 2018 and January 2019.

Vaccination
-----------
- Since Fri 8 Feb 2019, vaccination of primary health care workers has started in Rwampara, a new health zone in Ituri.
- Vaccination in this health zone is justified by the fact that Rwampara is located on the Bunia-Kisangani road, which is used by thousands of people from Beni. This vaccination of primary care providers in the Rwampara health zone is part of the preventive measures to limit the spread of the disease in the other provinces.
- Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 77 010 people have been vaccinated.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteurs Mary Marshall and Kunihiko Iizuka

[Helen Branswell (https://twitter.com/HelenBranswell)
There's a little bit more detail in today's #Ebola update from @MinSanteRDC about the 7 probable cases added to the case count yesterday. These were people -- obviously contacts of cases -- who became sick in Nov & Dec & died between Nov & Jan. All were from Katwa.

