[3] Local news
- Sat 9 Feb 2019. Fight against Ebola in Butembo: police rescue agents from response to a youth attack on Mutiri
[Radio Moto Butembo-Beni, in French, machine trans., edited]
http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5414

The response team responsible for supervision in health facilities was attacked by young people from cell Ngothe B Mutiri neighborhood this Sat 9 Feb 2019. According to the head of the hospital Dieu-merci, the visibility of this team marked by the presence of the vehicle would be the basis of this attack. "This is not the 1st time that supervisors have come here, they come to supervise every day without a truck, but no harm has ever been observed," said Kabuyaya Wakinywa, head of the targeted structure. In an interview with our reporter, this official draws up a balance of 120 US dollars taken from the body of its structure, and the damaged truck. The agents of the response team were saved thanks to the intervention of the police.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Mary Marshall

[This is an example of the unrest exacerbating conduct of providing health care and vaccination in the eastern DRC. Fortunately, the police were available to intervene. - Mod.LK]

- Sat 9 Feb 2019. Patient attendance decreases with the new modalities of free healthcare in Butembo
[Radio Moto Butembo-Beni, in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5415

After the new modalities of free healthcare, the attendance of patients has significantly decreased in health facilities. "With regard to the contract amendment since [16 Jan 2019], the movement of patients has become irregular within the structure, because there are certain diseases that have been discarded, and then there may have been a lot of conditions for care," said the health manager administrator in Katwa Health Zone.

[There is a suspect case now] and we will investigate to see if he is really sick of Ebola, " he added.

Since Wed 16 Jan 2019, we have reduced the package of services covered by free care in the health areas concerned.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Mary Marshall

[It is not clear why the services covered by free healthcare were reduced in January 2019, at a time when they were certainly needed, but could be a matter of not having the necessary financial resources. - Mod.LK

